{"TopicId":134838,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How To Stop Your Rocket Tipping Over ~ Tutorial","CreatedByName":"Eveeloo","CreatedById":160563,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-24T06:26:30Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Eveeloo","CreatedById":160563,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-24T06:26:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-top:0px;color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot here\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-30T19:08:52Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2016 07:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by KerbalSpace\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kiwi1960","CreatedById":81697,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-24T07:08:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI usually tip over after drinking too much.... just sayin... y\u0027know... and I dinna think pressing T will help... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood info.... I needed to know that.... I won\u0027t be using MechJeb any more.... not for launching...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-24T07:09:30Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2016 07:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by kiwi1960\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-24T07:31:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know what \u0022tippling\u0022 is.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-24T07:37:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeep in mind that this does not work in Career mode unless you have a pilot-class Kerbal that\u0027s already been to orbit and back once, or a probe core from a few hundred science points down the tree. So you won\u0027t be able to get around \u003Cem\u003Esome\u003C/em\u003E manual flying. Better learn how to do it right without relying on SAS! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Eveeloo","CreatedById":160563,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-24T08:45:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222471194\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134838\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458804669\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113764\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Foxster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Foxster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know what \u0022tippling\u0022 is.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits when your rocket goes up-side down\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hodari","CreatedById":157578,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-24T13:23:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, but no...this wasn\u0027t useful at all and neither was your \u0022How to get into orbit tutorial.\u00A0 Both VERY badly oversimplify things and leave out almost all of the relevant information.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you make a tutorial on not tipping over and have no mention of where to keep your center of mass?\u00A0 Or drag?\u00A0 Or any kind of aerodynamics at all?\u00A0 No mention of using fins?\u00A0 Nothing about when to limit your speed?\u00A0 Not even symmetry?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you do a tutorial on getting to orbit and not even mention the delta-V requirements or ascent profile?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Warzouz","CreatedById":140055,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-24T14:38:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you need SAS not to have your rocket flipping, then your rocket is badly designed or your ascent profile poorly execute. You shouldn\u0027t need SAS until 30 or 40km high.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, following prograde is not enough to save you from badly designed rockets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also agree that your tutorial is oversimplified and not really useful to a new player who need tips to go to LKO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, a very useful and detailed tutorial already exists\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/114664-105-rocket-ascent-profile-and-gravity-turn\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-24T14:47:07Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2016 02:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Warzouz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Eveeloo","CreatedById":160563,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T19:04:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;.;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E\u00A0im not making any more posts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex","CreatedById":75164,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T19:45:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLocked this thread up because it went pretty out of control. \u0022Tipped,\u0022 according to the OP, actually a very good description.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to remind some of the posters here that indeed, pressing the SAS button is a very good tip for helping your rocket not tip over. In fact, this step is so important that I\u0027m glad \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/160563-kerbalspace/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022160563\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/160563-kerbalspace/\u0022\u003E@KerbalSpace\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0took the time to tell everybody about it. After all, launching a huge rocket to, say, Jool, would be pretty difficult without the awesome SAS button. Also, kudos to \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/98962-streetwind/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002298962\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/98962-streetwind/\u0022\u003E@Streetwind\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for his excellent advice along with the OP\u0027s topic!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}